# host-lint is a tell detector, so a few of its own files legitimately embed the
# tells it detects. The per-file git-hook scan honors this list too (see main.rs),
# so these never need `--no-verify`. Every entry was checked line-by-line — each
# flag is an intended example/fixture or a test-harness false positive, never a real
# tell hiding in plain sight:
#   VOCABULARY.md / README.md / SKILL.md  — the detection spec + docs (tell examples)
#   test-integration.sh / lint-skill.sh   — test-harness scripts (fixtures; pass/fail
#                                            gate vocabulary trips the pass-synonym rule)
#   tests/                                 — proptest fixtures with tell strings
# src/lib.rs is NOT excluded: its 2 example comments were reworded so it no longer
# flags (it only carries advisory warns on rule examples), so a real tell there is
# still caught.
VOCABULARY.md
README.md
SKILL.md
test-integration.sh
lint-skill.sh
tests/
